content.text:
This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   - Build an interactive EV charging dashboard using the Monta Partner API (credentials provided: Client ID `47095201-e97d-4697-ae5a-d7914655f6cf`, Client Secret `184d8bdb-7820-4d1e-b364-fb61ee3e068b`)
   - Add a map view with all charger stations plotted and a heat map showing charge activity (weighted by sessions or kWh)
   - Fix the heat map (it was broken)
   - Add a **Utilization tab** showing: kWh/day, hours charging/day, utilization %, site rankings to identify high-performing sites for replication
   - Add a **Profitability tab** with cost model: $20/month/charger operating cost, $0.16/kWh electricity, $0.03/kWh revenue share with property owner — views at site level, charger level, and portfolio level
   - Add a **Revenue Payout tab** showing total revenue, property owner payout, electricity cost, operating cost, and site-level payout breakdown

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Monta Partner API (EV charging management platform)
   - OAuth2-style auth: POST `https://partner-api.monta.com/api/v1/auth/token` with `{clientId, clientSecret}` → returns `accessToken`
   - API pagination: `perPage=100` parameter; response has `meta.totalPageCount`, `meta.totalItemCount`, `meta.currentPage`
   - Correct API field names (discovered by live browser inspection):
     - Status: `state` (not `status`)
     - Energy: `consumedKwh` (not `kwh`/`energyKwh`/`energy`)
     - Coordinates: `location.coordinates.latitude` / `location.coordinates.longitude`
     - Power: `maxKW` (not `maxPower`)
     - Revenue per session: `price`
     - Pagination param: `perPage` (not `pageSize`)
   - 108 charge points total, 3,086 charge sessions total
   - Date filtering NOT supported server-side on `/charges` — must fetch all and filter client-side
   - Sites endpoint returns UNAUTHORIZED — must group by `siteId` field on charge points, derive site name from `location.address.address1 + city`
   - Heat map CDN fix: cdnjs URL returns 404; use `https://unpkg.com/leaflet.heat@0.2.0/dist/leaflet-heat.js`
   - Leaflet.js for interactive map with OpenStreetMap tiles
   - Chart.js 4.4.1 for all charts (bar, donut/doughnut, line)
   - Self-contained single HTML file dashboard (no backend needed, API calls made from browser)
   - Profitability formula: `profit = revenue - (kwh × $0.16) - (kwh × $0.03) - ($20 × numChargers × months)`

3. Files and Code Sections:
   - **`/sessions/zen-dreamy-mayer/mnt/outputs/monta-dashboard.html`** — The primary output file, a self-contained HTML dashboard
     - Started as a basic overview dashboard with KPIs and charts
     - Extended with a Map & Heat Map tab (Leaflet.js, Leaflet.heat)
     - All API field names corrected after live API inspection
     - Pagination fixed (`perPage` instead of `pageSize`, using `meta.totalPageCount`)
     - Date filtering moved to client-side (`filterDate()` function)
     - Currently being rewritten to add 5 tabs: Overview, Utilization, Profitability, Revenue Payout, Map

   Key functions in the latest version being written:
   ```javascript
   // Auth
   async function auth() {
     const r = await fetch(`${API}/auth/token`, {method:'POST', headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'}, body: JSON.stringify({clientId:CID, clientSecret:CSC})});
     const d = await r.json();
     token = d.accessToken;
   }

   // Pagination - correct params
   async function fetchAll(path, params={}, cb=null) {
     let res=[], page=0;
     while(true) {
       const d = await apiGet(path, {...params, page, perPage:100});
       const items = d.data || [];
       res = res.concat(items);
       const tp = d.meta?.totalPageCount ?? 1;
       if(cb) cb(res.length, d.meta?.totalItemCount);
       if(page+1 >= tp || !items.length) break;
       page++;
     }
     return res;
   }

   // Correct coordinate extraction
   function getCoords(obj) {
     const c = [
       [obj.location?.coordinates?.latitude, obj.location?.coordinates?.longitude],
       [obj.location?.latitude, obj.location?.longitude],
       [obj.latitude, obj.longitude]
     ];
     for(const[la,lo] of c) { /* validate and return */ }
   }

   // CP stats using correct field names
   function buildCPStats(charges) {
     charges.forEach(c => {
       s[id].kwh += c.consumedKwh ?? 0;  // NOT c.kwh
       s[id].revenue += c.price ?? 0;
     });
   }

   // Profitability calculation
   function calcP(rev, kwh, nCPs, nDays) {
     const elec = kwh * ELEC;      // 0.16
     const share = kwh * RSHARE;   // 0.03
     const ops = OPMO * nCPs * (nDays / 30.44);  // 20/mo
     const profit = rev - elec - share - ops;
     return {elec, share, ops, cost: elec+share+ops, profit, margin: rev>0 ? profit/rev : null};
   }

   // Site grouping (no sites endpoint - derive from CP siteId)
   function buildSiteMap(cps) {
     cps.forEach(cp => {
       const sid = cp.siteId || 'unknown';
       const a = cp.location?.address;
       const name = a ? [a.address1, a.city].filter(Boolean).join(', ') : `Site ${sid}`;
       // ...
     });
   }
   ```

4. Errors and Fixes:
   - **Wrong API field names across the board**: Initially guessed field names (`kwh`, `status`, `maxPower`, `lat/lng`). Fixed after inspecting live API responses via browser JavaScript: all corrected to `consumedKwh`, `state`, `maxKW`, `location.coordinates.latitude/longitude`
   - **Pagination broken — only 10 records fetched**: Was using `pageSize=100` (ignored by API, defaulted to 10/page). Fixed to `perPage=100`. Also fixed termination logic to use `meta.totalPageCount` instead of `data.total`
   - **Date filtering silently ignored by API**: Tried `startDate`/`endDate`, `from`/`to`, `startedFrom`/`startedTo` — all returned 3,086 regardless. Fixed by fetching all data once and filtering client-side with `filterDate()`
